    <name>Giotto Extended Mission</name>
    <type>Mission</type>
    <start_date>1990</start_date>
    <stop_date>1992</stop_date>
    <description>After encountering Halley's Comet at part of the Halley Armada in March 1986, ESA's Giotto spacecraft hibernated through an extended cruide period on its way to encountering comet 26P/Grigg-Skjellerup. It flew by the comet at a distance of 200km in July 1992.</description>
